               <note>
                  <date type="foundation">1623</date>
                  <ab type="history">Gannata ʾIyasus is a Catholic church located in <placeName ref="LOC1669Azazo">ʾAzazo</placeName> on the <placeName ref="LOC6546Wagan">ʾAṣe Wagan</placeName> hill. It was commissioned by <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                     <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</persName> in <date>1621</date>, built
                     by the Jesuit <persName ref="PRS7699Paez">Pedro Páez</persName> and consacrated
                     in <date>1623</date>. <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</persName> is
                     said to have laid the church's foundation stone and he was buried here. </ab>
               </note>
            </place>
